        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-12T00:38:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if A is being included into B, what is the word to describe what\u0027s happening with B? is it \"extended\"?",
      "parentUuid": "a3bf1dad_c4173b2d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "778de2a34908bd226ac5536df7464b37f6ec18af",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "78903e86_ebb33017",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/v1/recorder.proto",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-12T00:52:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Definitely related, but is that the actually the same connotation of what we\u0027re doing?\n\nSo for instance, if we have a CQ attempt that forms an invocation X, and we include in it an invocation Y from a builder, and then override the inclusion of Y into X with the inclusion of Z into X, did we /extend/ X with Z? Open question; again, I don\u0027t feel strongly either way",
      "parentUuid": "3dfa5ebf_5656bd0c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "778de2a34908bd226ac5536df7464b37f6ec18af",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c3fa602c_e3b4e54a",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/v1/recorder.proto",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-12T01:11:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "yes. Whether X-\u003eZ overrides something or not, X is being extended with Z\u0027s contents. Note that overriding is optional. The main point of this operation is to include X into Z, but we can overriding something along the way. In other words, i think the \"overriding\" aspect should not influence the choice the verb for this purpose",
      "parentUuid": "78903e86_ebb33017",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "778de2a34908bd226ac5536df7464b37f6ec18af",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7fa007ab_f6ac1d0b",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/v1/recorder.proto",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-12T01:20:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK. I personally wouldn\u0027t have considered that \"extending\" (regardless of overriding) because \"extend\" is somewhat ambiguous (could be extending deadline*, extending with more test results*, or if we add other fields to Invocation that can also be augmented, that could apply to those fields as well, or not).\n\nIf you think it fits, though, then that\u0027s fine by me (and feel free to mark the discussion as resolved as you like, or we can brainstorm some more; up to you).\n\n*yes, both of these examples could with reflection be understood not to be the function since we have UpdateInvocation and CreateTestResult; my point is just that \"extend\" may not be immediately intuitive",
      "parentUuid": "c3fa602c_e3b4e54a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 23
      },
